\pard\f0\fs28 Rhizome dictyostelic, with hairs, or with papillate or hairy scales. Hairs on leaves and rhizomes always unicellular, acicular. Petiole with U-shaped vascular strand; rhachis grooved but not interrupted to admit grooves of costae. Sori superficial, median or submarginal; indusium usually absent or caducous; spores bilateral.
